ADAPTING “A Suitable Boy”, Vikram Seth’s epic novel about marriage, politics and social upheaval in newly independent India, for the small screen was a labour of love for its director. Mira Nair talks to Anne McElvoy about why she worked with a white writer on this Indian classic, the eternal fascination of the matchmaker and the yoga pose that gets her in the right frame of mind. Runtime: 24 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/podcastoffer